{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"init(unix:)","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"unix","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib9IOChannelC4unixACSi_tcfc","roleHeading":"Initializer","symbolKind":"init","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/init(unix:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/init(unix:)"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":" given a file descriptor. On UNIX systems"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this works for plain files, pipes, and sockets."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"unix","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"fd"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The returned "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" has a reference count of 1."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default encoding for ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":" is UTF-8. If your application"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is reading output from a command using via pipe, you may need to set"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the encoding to the encoding of the current locale (see","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_get_charset()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()"},{"type":"text","text":" function."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"By default, the fd passed will not be closed when the final reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":" data structure is dropped."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to read raw binary data without interpretation, then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()"},{"text":" function with ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"encoding argument.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is available in GLib on Windows, too, but you should"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"avoid using it on Windows. The domain of file descriptors and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sockets overlap. There is no way for GLib to know which one you mean","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in case the argument you pass to this function happens to be both a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"valid file descriptor and socket. If that happens a warning is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"issued, and GLib assumes that it is the file descriptor you mean."}]}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"IOChannel","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"IOChannel","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into the main event loop (see [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]). Currently,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is only partially complete."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannel"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"title":"MainContext","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel/init(unix:)":{"title":"init(unix:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" given a file descriptor. On UNIX systems","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this works for plain files, pipes, and sockets."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/init(unix:)","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"unix","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/init(unix:)"}}}